  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    choco.IPretty, choco.kernel.solver.search.ISolutionDisplay, choco.kernel.solver.search.measure.IMeasures, choco.kernel.solver.search.measure.IOptimizationMeasures, choco.kernel.solver.search.measure.IPreSolveMeasures, choco.kernel.solver.search.measure.ISearchMeasures, choco.kernel.solver.search.measure.ISolutionMeasures, choco.kernel.solver.Solver, ReconfigurationProblem, CoreView

    public final class DefaultReconfigurationProblem
extends choco.cp.solver.CPSolver
implements ReconfigurationProblem
    A CSP to model a reconfiguration plan composed of time bounded actions. In this model, regarding to the current configuration and the sample destination configuration, the model create the different actions that aims to perform the transition to the destination configuration. In addition, several actions acting on the placement of the virtual machines can be added.
    Author:
    Fabien Hermenier

      • DefaultReconfigurationProblem

        public DefaultReconfigurationProblem(Configuration src,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> run,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> wait,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> sleep,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> stop)
                              throws PlanException
        Build a reconfiguration problem. All the VMs are candidate for management
        Parameters:
        src - the source configuration
        run - the virtual machines to run
        wait - the virtual machines that will stay waiting
        sleep - the virtual machines to turn into the sleeping state
        stop - the virtual machines to stop
        on - the nodes to turn on
        off - the nodes to turn off
        eval - the duration evaluator
        Throws:
        PlanException - if an error occurs

      • DefaultReconfigurationProblem

        public DefaultReconfigurationProblem(Configuration src,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> run,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> wait,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> sleep,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> stop,
                             ManagedElementSet<VirtualMachine> manageable)
                              throws PlanException
        Make a new model.
        Parameters:
        src - The source configuration. It must be viable.
        run - The set of virtual machines that must be running at the end of the process
        wait - The set of virtual machines that must be waiting at the end of the process
        sleep - The set of virtual machines that must be sleeping at the end of the process
        stop - The set of virtual machines that must be terminated at the end of the process
        manageable - the set of virtual machines to consider as manageable in the problem
        on - The set of nodes that must be online at the end of the process
        off - The set of nodes that must be offline at the end of the process
        eval - the evaluator to estimate the duration of an action.
        Throws:
        PlanException - if an error occurred while building the model
